{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BjY1osU1h218Wx6S8xY3Xa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n     4→**Session:** 8 (continuation from session 7 on 2026-03-23)\n     5→**Session start:** ~07:39 UTC\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1. Session Summary\n    10→\n    11→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages |\n    12→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n    13→| 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack | Epic 9 (Multi-Stack) | done (carryover from session 7) | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed |\n    14→| 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done — status: verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed |\n    15→\n    16→Both stories completed all pipeline stages (story creation, development, code review with fixes). Story 9-2 was carried over from session 7 (2026-03-23) where it went through create-story and dev-story; code review happened at the boundary. Story 10-1 was fully executed in this session.\n    17→\n    18→**Net progress:** Epic 9 fully closed (all 5 stories done). Epic 10 started — 1 of 5 stories done, 4 remain in backlog.\n    19→\n    20→---\n    21→\n    22→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    23→\n    24→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n    25→\n    26→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    27→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    28→| HIGH | 9-2 | `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — `detectStacks()` results lost on init | Yes |\n    29→| HIGH | 10-1 | `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` barrel file at 0% coverage — auto-registration never tested | Yes |\n    30→| HIGH | 10-1 | `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` at 17.64% coverage — 13 stub methods uncalled | Yes |\n    31→| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect | Yes |\n    32→| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` — no element type checking | Yes |\n    33→| MEDIUM | 9-2 | `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` | Yes |\n    34→| MEDIUM | 10-1 | Bare `catch {}` in registry.ts line 73 — readdirSync errors silently swallowed | Yes |\n    35→\n    36→Code review caught 7 HIGH/MEDIUM bugs across both stories. All were fixed in-session. The `init-project.ts` persistence bug (9-2) was the most impactful — multi-stack detection would have been silently broken at runtime.\n    37→\n    38→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    39→\n    40→1. **`stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]`** in `stack.test.ts` — readonly tuple workaround. Minor, localized to tests.\n    41→2. **`migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName`** without validating against known stack names (9-2, LOW, not fixed). Invalid stack names in old state files would pass migration unchecked.\n    42→3. **`recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()`** — double detection (9-2, LOW, not fixed). Performance waste, not a correctness issue.\n    43→\n    44→### Code Quality Concerns\n    45→\n    46→1. **`StackDetection` type duplicated** between `registry.ts` and `stack-detect.ts` (10-1, MEDIUM, deferred to story 10-5). Expected — the old and new codepaths coexist until consumer migration.\n    47→2. **`_resetRegistry` test-only utility leaking into public barrel export** (10-1, LOW, not fixed). Should be conditionally exported or moved to test helpers.\n    48→3. **Parallel detection codepaths** — `stack-detect.ts` retains hardcoded detection while `registry.ts` has marker-based detection. Two ways to detect stacks coexist until story 10-5.\n    49→4. **~10 pre-existing TS compilation errors** in test files (bridge, run, stack, status, teardown, deps, sync). Not from this session but noted by dev agents.\n    50→\n    51→### Verification Gaps\n    52→\n    53→- **`recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path for `stacks` field** not directly unit-tested — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir (9-2).\n    54→- **`init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field** after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks (9-2).\n    55→- Both stories currently in `verifying` status — final verification pass not yet completed.\n    56→\n    57→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n    58→\n    59→- No sandbox, permission, or CLI issues reported this session.\n    60→- Pre-existing TS compilation errors (~10 test files) continue to be noise but do not block execution."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0167PgbvxGvH7NwRVf7SRSLy","session_id":"6707468c-554d-4568-9ea5-0d04d4a85f59","uuid":"18c28253-293d-4730-a7e6-fb847e89399b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:14:36.236Z"}
