{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EPL4eJAP5W5qUxFXY5uuFc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"123 files, all passed. The test isolation issue when running a subset is a pre-existing problem (tests share the project root's sprint-state.json). The full suite works because Vitest isolates workers.\n\nHere is the summary of all changes made:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/types/state.ts` -- Renamed `SprintState` to `SprintStateV1`, created `SprintStateV2` with `version: 2`, new fields (`retries`, `flagged`, `epics`, `session`, `observability`), created `EpicState`, `SessionState`, `ObservabilityState` interfaces, `SprintStateAny` union, and `SprintState` alias for `SprintStateV2`.\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts` -- `defaultState()` returns v2 with `version: 2` and all new fields initialized. `getSprintState()` checks version field: if 2 returns as-is (merging defaults), if 1 or missing calls `migrateV1ToV2()` and writes result atomically.\n\n3. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/migration.ts` -- Added `migrateV1ToV2()` that reads `.story_retries` (space-separated), `.flagged_stories` (one per line), and `ralph/status.json` to populate v2 fields. Does NOT delete source files. Updated `migrateFromOldFormat()` to output v2. Added `parseStoryRetriesRecord()` and `parseFlaggedStoriesList()` helpers.\n\n4. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/retry-state.ts` -- Refactored all functions to read/write `sprint-state.json` via `getSprintState()`/`writeStateAtomic()` instead of flat files. `dir` parameter kept for backward compatibility but not used.\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` -- Added 7 new tests for v1-to-v2 migration: with retries/flagged files, without them, with ralph/status.json, missing version field, malformed retries, file non-deletion, and existing migrateFromOldFormat tests updated for v2 output.\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/retry-state.test.ts` -- Rewritten to test against sprint-state.json instead of flat files, using `process.chdir` for isolation.\n\n7. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/retry.test.ts` -- Rewritten to use sprint-state.json instead of .story_retries/.flagged_stories files.\n\n8. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/types/__tests__/state.test.ts` -- Updated for v2 schema, added tests for `SprintStateV1`, `SprintStateV2`, `SprintStateAny`, `EpicState`, `SessionState`, `ObservabilityState`.\n\n9. Updated test fixtures in `feedback.test.ts`, `reporter.test.ts`, `selector.test.ts`, `state.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`, `run-progress.test.ts`, `fix-generator.test.ts`, `validation-runner.test.ts` to use v2 schema.\n\n10. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning.md` -- Status changed to `review`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing test isolation problem**: Tests that write to the project root's `sprint-state.json` (state.test.ts, migration.test.ts, index.test.ts) interfere with each other when run in the same Vitest batch without full worker isolation. This is pre-existing and not introduced by this story. The full `npm test` run uses proper isolation and passes cleanly.\n\n- **`dir` parameter is vestigial in retry-state.ts**: Per the story spec, the `dir` parameter is kept on all retry-state functions for backward compatibility but is completely unused. The functions now read from `process.cwd()/sprint-state.json`. This is deliberate tech debt documented in the story. Callers like `retry.ts` still pass `dir` with no effect.\n\n- **Pre-existing TS errors (87 total)**: All from unrelated test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, teardown.test.ts, deps.test.ts, etc.). Zero new errors introduced.\n\n- **Real sprint-state.json on disk still has `version: 1`**: The live `sprint-state.json` in the project root currently has `version: 1`. On next `getSprintState()` call (e.g., when ralph runs), it will auto-migrate to v2. This is the intended behavior per the story's migration strategy."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7b7fb214933c7391 (use SendMessage with to: 'a7b7fb214933c7391' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 132828\ntool_uses: 100\nduration_ms: 809451</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6707468c-554d-4568-9ea5-0d04d4a85f59","uuid":"f2797f6e-44e0-409a-a52b-34b83983afd5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:34:07.412Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a7b7fb214933c7391","content":[{"type":"text","text":"123 files, all passed. The test isolation issue when running a subset is a pre-existing problem (tests share the project root's sprint-state.json). The full suite works because Vitest isolates workers.\n\nHere is the summary of all changes made:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/types/state.ts` -- Renamed `SprintState` to `SprintStateV1`, created `SprintStateV2` with `version: 2`, new fields (`retries`, `flagged`, `epics`, `session`, `observability`), created `EpicState`, `SessionState`, `ObservabilityState` interfaces, `SprintStateAny` union, and `SprintState` alias for `SprintStateV2`.\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts` -- `defaultState()` returns v2 with `version: 2` and all new fields initialized. `getSprintState()` checks version field: if 2 returns as-is (merging defaults), if 1 or missing calls `migrateV1ToV2()` and writes result atomically.\n\n3. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/migration.ts` -- Added `migrateV1ToV2()` that reads `.story_retries` (space-separated), `.flagged_stories` (one per line), and `ralph/status.json` to populate v2 fields. Does NOT delete source files. Updated `migrateFromOldFormat()` to output v2. Added `parseStoryRetriesRecord()` and `parseFlaggedStoriesList()` helpers.\n\n4. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/retry-state.ts` -- Refactored all functions to read/write `sprint-state.json` via `getSprintState()`/`writeStateAtomic()` instead of flat files. `dir` parameter kept for backward compatibility but not used.\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` -- Added 7 new tests for v1-to-v2 migration: with retries/flagged files, without them, with ralph/status.json, missing version field, malformed retries, file non-deletion, and existing migrateFromOldFormat tests updated for v2 output.\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/retry-state.test.ts` -- Rewritten to test against sprint-state.json instead of flat files, using `process.chdir` for isolation.\n\n7. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/retry.test.ts` -- Rewritten to use sprint-state.json instead of .story_retries/.flagged_stories files.\n\n8. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/types/__tests__/state.test.ts` -- Updated for v2 schema, added tests for `SprintStateV1`, `SprintStateV2`, `SprintStateAny`, `EpicState`, `SessionState`, `ObservabilityState`.\n\n9. Updated test fixtures in `feedback.test.ts`, `reporter.test.ts`, `selector.test.ts`, `state.test.ts`, `index.test.ts`, `run-progress.test.ts`, `fix-generator.test.ts`, `validation-runner.test.ts` to use v2 schema.\n\n10. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning.md` -- Status changed to `review`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing test isolation problem**: Tests that write to the project root's `sprint-state.json` (state.test.ts, migration.test.ts, index.test.ts) interfere with each other when run in the same Vitest batch without full worker isolation. This is pre-existing and not introduced by this story. The full `npm test` run uses proper isolation and passes cleanly.\n\n- **`dir` parameter is vestigial in retry-state.ts**: Per the story spec, the `dir` parameter is kept on all retry-state functions for backward compatibility but is completely unused. The functions now read from `process.cwd()/sprint-state.json`. This is deliberate tech debt documented in the story. Callers like `retry.ts` still pass `dir` with no effect.\n\n- **Pre-existing TS errors (87 total)**: All from unrelated test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, teardown.test.ts, deps.test.ts, etc.). Zero new errors introduced.\n\n- **Real sprint-state.json on disk still has `version: 1`**: The live `sprint-state.json` in the project root currently has `version: 1`. On next `getSprintState()` call (e.g., when ralph runs), it will auto-migrate to v2. This is the intended behavior per the story's migration strategy."}],"totalDurationMs":809451,"totalTokens":132828,"totalToolUseCount":100,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":182,"cache_read_input_tokens":131401,"output_tokens":1244,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_c